# Cursor Rules for Personal Blog

## Project Overview

This is a personal blog built with Next.js 15 and MDX. The site is deployed at www.waynewen.com via Vercel with GitHub integration.

## Tech Stack

- Next.js 15 (App Router)
- React 19
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- MDX for blog content
- Vercel for deployment

## Package Manager

Use **npm** exclusively. Do not use yarn, pnpm, or bun.

```bash
npm install      # Install dependencies
npm run dev      # Development server
npm run build    # Production build
npm run start    # Production server
npm run lint     # Linting
```

## Project Structure

```
src/
├── app/           # Next.js App Router pages
├── components/    # React components
│   └── mdx/       # MDX-specific components
├── config/        # Site and blog configuration
├── content/       # MDX blog posts
│   └── blog/      # Blog post files
├── fonts/         # Custom fonts (Atkinson Hyperlegible)
└── lib/           # Utility functions
    └── mdx/       # MDX processing utilities
```

## Coding Conventions

Follow Next.js best practices:

- Use functional components with hooks
- Use named exports for components
- Use PascalCase for component files and names
- Use camelCase for utility functions and variables
- Prefer TypeScript interfaces over types for object shapes
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling (no CSS modules or styled-components)

## Content

Blog posts are MDX files in `src/content/blog/` with frontmatter:

```mdx
---
title: "Post Title"
date: "YYYY-MM-DD"
description: "Brief description"
---
```

## Scope

This repository is exclusively for the personal blog. Do not add features unrelated to blogging functionality.

## Key Files

- `src/config/site.ts` - Site-wide configuration
- `src/config/blog.ts` - Blog-specific configuration
- `src/lib/mdx/utils.ts` - MDX processing utilities
- `src/components/mdx/` - Custom MDX components
